# Northbridge UI Standard

A feature is **not complete** unless it passes all of the following:

## Responsive review

1. **Desktop review** — layout, typography, spacing, and interactions verified at desktop breakpoints.
2. **Mobile review** — verified on small screens (≤640px); no clipped content or broken navigation.
3. **Tablet review** — verified at tablet breakpoints (md/lg); no awkward reflows or orphaned elements.
4. **No horizontal scroll** — no `overflow-x` on any customer-facing screen; test with long words, tables, and forms.

## Touch & navigation

5. **Large tap targets** — interactive elements ≥44×44px (buttons, links, menu items, form controls).
6. **CAT reachable** — CAT is accessible from every customer-facing screen without dead ends.

## Mobile UX

7. **Primary CTA visible on mobile** — the main call-to-action is visible above the fold or immediately obvious without excessive scrolling.
8. **Forms usable on mobile** — inputs are full-width, labels visible, keyboard types correct, submit reachable.
9. **Dashboards readable on mobile** — data tables/cards stack or scroll intentionally; no unreadable micro-text.

## Build quality

10. **Build + lint pass** — `npm run build` and `npm run lint` succeed with zero errors before marking done.

## Before finishing UI work

- Manually spot-check desktop, tablet, and mobile viewports.
- Confirm Header nav and primary CTA paths work on all breakpoints.
- Run build and lint; fix all failures before reporting the feature complete.
